    <body>
      <trans-unit id="8408" identifier="36710e8e1305fd9b7986bb20340cf7af">
        <source>Make variables called:</source>
        <target>crwdns8408:0crwdne8408:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8409" identifier="b42a9f98b8f02083c7b712d1979c309e">
        <source>“number” and set its value to the input number given by the end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns8409:0crwdne8409:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8410" identifier="ab341e1727206ecf539a297c703b0faf">
        <source>“bit value” and set its value to ‘1’.
Find the smallest bit value which is larger than the “number” by
doubling value of “bit value” until it is bigger than the “number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8410:0crwdne8410:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8411" identifier="afde2476b038f321d802539f2dd1b562">
        <source>“cards” is a string variable and stores the binary cards needed (‘B’
for black cards and ‘W’ for white cards).</source>
        <target>crwdns8411:0crwdne8411:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8412" identifier="c64cc1cdd473ccc7f1b2bf71b1c41067">
        <source>Set the variable “bit value” to 1 and find the smallest “bit value” which
is larger than “number” by multiplying “bit value” by 2 (Use the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:() * ()&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators” to multiply the “bit value” by
2) until it is larger than “number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8412:0crwdne8412:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8413" identifier="8c7a6ce24b080a1cf2de51961db232fc">
        <source>You can do this by using a &lt;code&gt;scratch:repeat until &amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; loop.</source>
        <target>crwdns8413:0crwdne8413:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8414" identifier="df936020f7a609b0f32afc6845a560f2">
        <source>Now divide the “bit value” by 2 and check if “number” is greater than or
equal to “bit value”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8414:0crwdne8414:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8415" identifier="b1bc05c2438e420f9fb98b19dde5f06f">
        <source>If it is, add ‘W’ to string variable “cards” and subtract “bit value”
from the “number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8415:0crwdne8415:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8416" identifier="2d9cf123b19f34672085fff7d46f0863">
        <source>If not, add ‘B’ to string variable “cards”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8416:0crwdne8416:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8417" identifier="036b9987faa22fafc1e4a064358127df">
        <source>Repeat until “bit value” is equal to 1.</source>
        <target>crwdns8417:0crwdne8417:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8418" identifier="253f2779c39dc44e9c19d62ef465d51f">
        <source>Display the value of “cards” as the output.</source>
        <target>crwdns8418:0crwdne8418:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8419" identifier="af40c965e55d19d841a8988be6e8d291">
        <source>Test your program with some values on the boundaries (for example test it
with numbers 255 and 256).</source>
        <target>crwdns8419:0crwdne8419:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
